Comment.Text: This part of the scenario is responsible for showing the signals and the target versus non-target figures with confidence bound
When you press 'escape' in the external application, it will stop it. The application send back through the tagging system the End of experiment stimulis (182) that stops the scenario.

Temporal filtering and spatial filtering is done before epoching. Epochs are extracted based on the stimulation identifier 195 (corresponding to a flash). The classifier outputs the probability for each flash. This result is written in shared memory which is read by the p300 stimulator. This probability is then combined in the evidence accumulator module of the external application with the info about the symbols being flashed. It then computes the probabilities for each symbol and outputs the most probable one when a certain threshold is reached.
This scenario only record data for later comparisons, not of any use for actual BCI.
